{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875537682,"sessionID":"ses_285935aa0ffeAkIfvQFvlm4sNA","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6e3ac0001Pu1CRdNRU3I0IY","messageID":"msg_d7a6cebca0010Xnjq2oqN3jaAh","sessionID":"ses_285935aa0ffeAkIfvQFvlm4sNA","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ad5927927fd844429effcc56a5b0c0c1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n**Module**: `cmd/cli`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes provider for agent deployment, enabling both standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service resources and AgentCube Custom Resources (AgentRuntime) for agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe Kubernetes provider enables the AgentCube CLI to deploy and manage agents on Kubernetes clusters using two deployment strategies:\n\n1. **Standard K8s Provider**: Creates native Kubernetes `Deployment` and `NodePort Service` resources\n2. **AgentCube Provider**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resources (CRD) managed by the AgentCube operator\n\nBoth providers share common interfaces through the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` service classes, which are integrated into the CLI via `PublishRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes.\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n├── cli/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   └── main.py                    # Typer CLI commands (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n├── models/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions dataclass\n├── runtime/\n│   ├── __init__.py                # Runtime exports\n│   ├── pack_runtime.py            # PackRuntime class\n│   ├── build_runtime.py           # BuildRuntime class\n│   ├── publish_runtime.py         # PublishRuntime class\n│   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # InvokeRuntime class\n│   └── status_runtime.py          # StatusRuntime class\n├── services/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── metadata_service.py        # AgentMetadata model & persistence\n│   ├── docker_service.py          # Docker image operations\n│   ├── k8s_provider.py            # KubernetesProvider (standard K8s)\n│   └── agentcube_provider.py      # AgentCubeProvider (AgentRuntime CR)\n└── operations/\n    └── __init__.py                # Placeholder for future operations\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  CLI (Typer)    │\n│  - pack         │\n│  - build        │\n│  - publish      │\n│  - invoke       │\n│  - status       │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n         ├──> PublishRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n         │                     │    (Deployment + Service)\n         │                     │\n         │                     └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n         │                          (AgentRuntime CR)\n         │\n         ├──> StatusRuntime ──┬──> KubernetesProvider ──> K8s API\n         │                    │    (Deployment/Service status)\n         │                    │\n         │                    └──> AgentCubeProvider ──> K8s API\n         │                         (AgentRuntime CR status)\n         │\n         ├──> InvokeRuntime ──┬──> Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n         │                    │\n         │                    └──> Router HTTP (AgentRuntime)\n         │\n         └──> MetadataService ──> agent_metadata.yaml\n\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  DockerService  │\n│  - build_image  │\n│  - push_image   │\n└─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Selection\n\nProvider is selected via the `--provider` CLI option:\n\n- `--provider agentcube` (default): Uses `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR\n- `--provider k8s`: Uses `KubernetesProvider` for standard Deployment/Service\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, validator\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    language: str = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = 8080\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    version: Optional[str] = None\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n\n    @validator('language')\n    def validate_language(cls, v):\n        if v.lower() not in ['python', 'java']:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @validator('build_mode')\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n        if v.lower() not in ['local', 'cloud']:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @validator('port')\n    def validate_port(cls, v):\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in cls.__dataclass_fields__})\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment Info\n\n```python\n{\n    \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n    \"deployment_name\": str,\n    \"service_name\": str,\n    \"namespace\": str,\n    \"replicas\": int,\n    \"container_port\": int,\n    \"node_port\": int,\n    \"service_url\": str,\n    \"status\": str,\n    \"last_updated\": str\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### KubernetesProvider Interface\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Interface\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n```\n\n### PublishRuntime Interface\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass ProviderError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for provider operations\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass KubernetesError(ProviderError):\n    \"\"\"Kubernetes provider specific errors\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass AgentCubeProviderError(ProviderError):\n    \"\"\"AgentCube provider specific errors\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DeploymentTimeoutError(KubernetesError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when deployment fails to become ready within timeout\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n1. **Docker Unavailability**: Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n2. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**: Raise `KubernetesError` with detailed message\n3. **Missing Prerequisites**: Raise `ValueError` with clear instructions\n4. **Deployment Timeout**: Raise `TimeoutError` after configured timeout\n5. **CR Not Found**: Return `None` or appropriate status indicator\n6. **Validation Failures**: Raise `ValueError` with field-specific details\n\n### Error Recovery\n\n- **Namespace Creation**: Auto-create namespace if it doesn't exist\n- **Resource Updates**: Use `patch` instead of `create` to allow idempotent operations\n- **Session Cleanup**: Ensure sessions are deleted on context manager exit\n- **Rollback on Failure**: Revert version increment if build fails\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```python\ntests/\n├── test_k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider tests\n├── test_agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider tests\n├── test_publish_runtime.py       # PublishRuntime tests\n├── test_status_runtime.py        # StatusRuntime tests\n├── test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n└── fixtures/\n    ├── test_agent_metadata.yaml\n    └── mock_k8s_responses.py\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider Tests**:\n   - Namespace creation and validation\n   - Deployment creation with various configurations\n   - Service creation with NodePort assignment\n   - Status retrieval for different deployment states\n   - Resource deletion with proper cleanup\n   - Name sanitization (DNS-1123 compliance)\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider Tests**:\n   - AgentRuntime CR creation\n   - Environment variable injection (WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL)\n   - Readiness probe configuration\n   - CR status retrieval\n\n3. **PublishRuntime Tests**:\n   - Provider selection logic\n   - Image preparation (local vs cloud)\n   - Metadata updates after deployment\n   - Error handling for missing prerequisites\n\n4. **Integration Tests**:\n   - Full publish flow with mock Kubernetes API\n   - Status check after successful deployment\n   - Error propagation through the stack\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n\n- Use `unittest.mock` for Kubernetes API calls\n- Use `pytest-mock` for fixtures and side effects\n- Mock Docker SDK for build/push operations\n- Use `httpx.MockTransport` for HTTP client testing\n\n### Test Coverage\n\nTarget >80% coverage for:\n- `k8s_provider.py`\n- `agentcube_provider.py`\n- `publish_runtime.py`\n- `status_runtime.py`\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### Kubernetes API Integration\n\n**Kubernetes Client Initialization**:\n```python\nfrom kubernetes import client, config\n\ndef _get_k8s_client(kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None):\n    if kubeconfig:\n        config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n    else:\n        config.load_incluster_config()\n    return client.AppsV1Api(), client.CoreV1Api(), client.CustomObjectsApi()\n```\n\n**Kubernetes API Endpoints**:\n\n| Resource | Type | Endpoint |\n|----------|------|----------|\n| Deployment | `apps/v1` | `/apis/apps/v1/namespaces/{ns}/deployments/{name}` |\n| Service | `core/v1` | `/api/v1/namespaces/{ns}/services/{name}` |\n| Namespace | `core/v1` | `/api/v1/namespaces/{name}` |\n| AgentRuntime | Custom | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}` |\n\n### Docker Service Integration\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n```\n\n### Metadata Service Integration\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n```\n\n### CLI Integration\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n) -> None:\n    try:\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n        workspace_path = Path(workspace)\n        result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **locals())\n        console.print(f\"[green]Agent published successfully![/green]\")\n        console.print(f\"Agent ID: {result['agent_id']}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required Dependencies (from pyproject.toml)\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\n\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\n```\n\n### Python Version\n\n- `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n\n### External Services\n\n- **Kubernetes Cluster**: Access via kubeconfig or in-cluster config\n- **Container Registry**: For image push operations (optional for local testing)\n- **Docker Daemon**: Required for local image building\n\n## Documentation\n\n### User Documentation\n\n1. **Installation Guide**:\n   - Prerequisites (kubectl, Docker, Python 3.10+)\n   - Package installation: `pip install agentcube-cli[k8s]`\n   - Kubernetes cluster setup\n\n2. **Getting Started**:\n   - Creating an agent workspace\n   - Packing an agent: `kubectl-agentcube pack`\n   - Building an agent: `kubectl-agentcube build`\n   - Publishing to Kubernetes: `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n\n3. **Provider Documentation**:\n   - **Standard K8s Provider**: Using Deployment/Service resources\n   - **AgentCube Provider**: Using AgentRuntime CRDs\n   - Provider comparison and selection guide\n\n4. **Command Reference**:\n   - `kubectl-agentcube publish` --provider k8s --namespace default --replicas 3\n   - `kubectl-agentcube publish` --provider agentcube --node-port 30080\n\n### Developer Documentation\n\n1. **Architecture Overview**:\n   - Provider abstraction layer\n   - Kubernetes API interaction patterns\n   - Error handling strategy\n\n2. **API Reference**:\n   - `KubernetesProvider` class documentation\n   - `AgentCubeProvider` class documentation\n   - `PublishRuntime` integration\n\n3. **Contributing Guide**:\n   - Running tests: `pytest tests/`\n   - Code style: `ruff check agentcube/`\n   - Type checking: `mypy agentcube/`\n\n### Code Documentation\n\n- All public methods must have docstrings (Google style)\n- Complex logic must have inline comments\n- Type hints for all function signatures\n- Example usage in docstrings for key classes\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Kubernetes Authentication\n\n1. **Kubeconfig Security**:\n   - Support multiple authentication methods (token, cert, exec)\n   - Never log or print kubeconfig contents\n   - Validate kubeconfig file permissions\n\n2. **In-Cluster Configuration**:\n   - Use service account tokens when running in-cluster\n   - Validate service account permissions\n   - Implement RBAC requirements documentation\n\n### Credential Management\n\n1. **Registry Credentials**:\n   - Store securely in agent_metadata.yaml (file permissions)\n   - Support environment variables for sensitive values\n   - Never log credentials to stdout/stderr\n\n2. **Session Tokens**:\n   - Store session_id in metadata (optional, may be sensitive)\n   - Clear session_id on context manager exit\n   - Support token rotation for long-running sessions\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\n**For Standard K8s Provider**:\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-cli\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"namespaces\", \"services\", \"pods\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"apps\"]\n  resources: [\"deployments\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n**For AgentCube Provider**:\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-cli-cr\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n### Network Security\n\n1. **Registry Access**:\n   - Support HTTPS-only registry connections\n   - Validate SSL certificates\n   - Support proxy configuration for secure environments\n\n2. **Kubernetes API Access**:\n   - Prefer HTTPS for cluster communication\n   - Support custom CA bundles\n   - Validate API server certificates\n\n### Data Protection\n\n1. **Metadata File**:\n   - Set restrictive file permissions (0600)\n   - Exclude from version control (.gitignore)\n   - Support encryption for sensitive fields (future enhancement)\n\n2. **Logging**:\n   - Redact sensitive information from logs\n   - Avoid logging full metadata contents\n   - Use structured logging with sensitive field redaction\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n### Short-term Enhancements (0-3 months)\n\n1. **Rolling Updates**:\n   - Implement zero-downtime deployments\n   - Support rolling update strategies\n   - Rollback capabilities\n\n2. **Health Checks**:\n   - Enhanced readiness/liveness probe configuration\n   - Custom health check endpoints\n   - Health check status reporting\n\n3. **Resource Management**:\n   - Resource limits and requests configuration\n   - HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler) support\n   - VPA (Vertical Pod Autoscaler) integration\n\n### Medium-term Enhancements (3-6 months)\n\n1. **Multi-Cluster Support**:\n   - Deploy to multiple Kubernetes clusters\n   - Cluster selection via CLI flags\n   - Multi-cluster status aggregation\n\n2. **Advanced Deployment Strategies**:\n   - Blue-Green deployments\n   - Canary deployments\n   - Traffic splitting support\n\n3. **Observability Integration**:\n   - Prometheus metrics integration\n   - Distributed tracing support\n   - Custom resource metrics\n\n### Long-term Enhancements (6+ months)\n\n1. **GitOps Integration**:\n   - ArgoCD/Flux integration\n   - Git-based deployment manifests\n   - Automated synchronization\n\n2. **Server-Side Apply**:\n   - Kubernetes server-side apply support\n   - Conflict resolution strategies\n   - Multi-ownership support\n\n3. **Policy Enforcement**:\n   - OPA Gatekeeper integration\n   - Admission webhook support\n   - Policy validation hooks\n\n4. **Cross-Cloud Support**:\n   - EKS, GKE, AKS specific optimizations\n   - Cloud provider resource management\n   - Cloud-native feature integration\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider` class with all methods\n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider` class with all methods\n- [ ] Update `PublishRuntime` to support both providers\n- [ ] Update `StatusRuntime` to support both providers\n- [ ] Add provider selection logic in CLI\n- [ ] Implement namespace validation and creation\n- [ ] Add comprehensive error handling\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `KubernetesProvider`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `AgentCubeProvider`\n- [ ] Write integration tests for publish flow\n- [ ] Add type hints to all public methods\n- [ ] Add docstrings to all public methods\n- [ ] Update user documentation\n- [ ] Create RBAC manifests\n- [ ] Add security validations\n- [ ] Implement logging and monitoring hooks","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","time":{"start":1775875537628,"end":1775875537678}}}}
